@12919    = ~Inconsequence +3~
@12920    = ~This hammer was made by a self-styled prophet of providential rejection. His name was Phellep, and he believed that the actions of the individual were of no consequence to the fate of humanity as a whole. As a result, he rejected concepts of good and evil, instead adopting an attitude of enforced indifference and abstention from social, moral, and political activity. The hammer he carried with him was used to pound on the doors of churches, what he called "the dens of fools and mindless men."

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1d8 + 3
Attack Bonus:  +3
Enchantment:  +3
Damage Type:  Bludgeoning
Special:
  Good: +1d6 damage against evil creatures. Counts as a good-aligned weapon.
  Evil: +1d6 damage against good creatures. Counts as an evil-aligned weapon.
  Spellward: Immunity to the spells Holy Smite, Unholy Blight, Holy Word, and Blasphemy
Weight: 4 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Hammer
Type:  One-handed~
