@12923    = ~Foolsmiter +2~
@12924    = ~The Foolsmiter has a huge stone head in the shape of a rectangular block. Faint traces of gore and blood are on all sides of the hammer's head. The shaft is of a thick wood that looks too weak to support the hammer head's weight. The Foolsmiter has a unique enchantment: it hits harder against foes that are stupider than the wielder. However, the enchantment has another twist: if the wielder is stupider than the target of an attack, the wielder takes damage as well.

Damage:  1d8 + 2
Attack Bonus:  +2
Enchantment:  +2
Damage Type:  Bludgeoning
Special:
  Foolsmiting: If the wielder has a higher Intelligence bonus than the target, the hammer deals extra damage to the target equal to the difference in Intelligence bonus between the wielder and the target. If the wielder has a lower Intelligence bonus than the target, they take the damage instead.
Weight: 15 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Hammer
Type:  One-handed~
